/-!
# International Mathematical Competition 2009, Problem 10
(Day 2, Problem 5)

Let `M` be the vector space of `m √ó p` real matrices. For a vector subspace
`S ‚äÜ M`, denote by `őī(S)` the dimension of the vector space generated by all
columns of all matrices in `S`.

Say that a vector subspace `T ‚äÜ M` is a *covering matrix space* if
`‚čÉ_{A ‚ąą T, A ‚Č† 0} ker A = ‚ĄĚ^p`.

Such a `T` is *minimal* if it does not contain a proper vector subspace
`S ‚äā T` which is also a covering matrix space.

(a) Let `T` be a minimal covering matrix space and let `n = dim T`.
Prove that `őī(T) ‚Č§ n choose 2`.

(b) Prove that for every positive integer `n` we can find `m` and `p`, and a
minimal covering matrix space `T` as above such that `dim T = n` and
`őī(T) = n choose 2`.

The mathematical proof outline:
(a) In any covering subspace `S`, find `A ‚ąą S` with `rk A ‚Č§ dim S - 1`.
Take a minimal subspace `S‚āÄ ‚äÜ S`, fix a hyperplane `S' ‚äā S‚āÄ`. By
minimality, `S'` is not covering, so there is `u` with `ŌĄ(u) ‚Č† 0` for all
nonzero `ŌĄ ‚ąą S'`. The space `V = S'(u)` has dimension `s - 1`. There is
`A ‚ąą S‚āÄ ‚ąĖ S'` with `Au = 0` (since `S‚āÄ` is covering). One shows
`Im A ‚äā V`, otherwise a generic perturbation yields a non-covering
contradiction. Iterate this to get a decomposition with the binomial bound.

(b) Take rows indexed by pairs `(i,j)` with `1 ‚Č§ i < j ‚Č§ n`. For
`u ‚ąą ‚ĄĚ‚ĀŅ`, let `A(u)` have entries `A(u)_{(i,j),k} = u_i` if `k = j`,
`-u_j` if `k = i`, and `0` otherwise. Then `ker A(u) = ‚ĄĚ¬∑u`, so
`T = {A(u) : u ‚ąą ‚ĄĚ‚ĀŅ}` is minimal covering, and the columns hit each
standard basis vector in `‚ĄĚ^{n choose 2}`.
-/

namespace Imc2009P10

open Matrix LinearMap Submodule

/-- A subspace `T` of `m √ó p` real matrices is a *covering matrix space* if
the union of kernels of nonzero elements equals all of `‚ĄĚ^p`. We phrase this
in matrix-space form: every `v : Fin p ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ` lies in the kernel of some
nonzero matrix `A ‚ąą T` (viewed as the linear map `mulVec`). -/
def IsCovering {m p : ‚Ąē} (T : Submodule ‚ĄĚ (Matrix (Fin m) (Fin p) ‚ĄĚ)) : Prop :=
  ‚ąÄ v : Fin p ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ, ‚ąÉ A : Matrix (Fin m) (Fin p) ‚ĄĚ,
    A ‚ąą T ‚ąß A ‚Č† 0 ‚ąß A.mulVec v = 0

/-- A covering matrix space `T` is *minimal* if no proper subspace of `T` is
also covering. -/
def IsMinimalCovering {m p : ‚Ąē} (T : Submodule ‚ĄĚ (Matrix (Fin m) (Fin p) ‚ĄĚ)) :
    Prop :=
  IsCovering T ‚ąß ‚ąÄ S : Submodule ‚ĄĚ (Matrix (Fin m) (Fin p) ‚ĄĚ),
    S ‚Č§ T ‚Üí S ‚Č† T ‚Üí ¬¨ IsCovering S

/-- The "column span" `őī(T)`: the dimension of the subspace of `‚ĄĚ^m` spanned
by all columns of all matrices in `T`. We define the column span as the
submodule of `‚ĄĚ^m` generated by the set of all columns of all `A ‚ąą T`. -/
noncomputable def colSpan {m p : ‚Ąē}
    (T : Submodule ‚ĄĚ (Matrix (Fin m) (Fin p) ‚ĄĚ)) :
    Submodule ‚ĄĚ (Fin m ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ) :=
  Submodule.span ‚ĄĚ {v : Fin m ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ | ‚ąÉ A ‚ąą T, ‚ąÉ j : Fin p, v = fun i => A i j}

/-- `őī(T)` is the dimension of the column span of `T`. -/
noncomputable def delta {m p : ‚Ąē}
    (T : Submodule ‚ĄĚ (Matrix (Fin m) (Fin p) ‚ĄĚ)) : ‚Ąē :=
  Module.finrank ‚ĄĚ (colSpan T)

/-- The binomial coefficient `n choose 2`. -/
def binom2 (n : ‚Ąē) : ‚Ąē := n.choose 2

